Sentencas: Large-size, 8 cm x 8 cm, NiO-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (Ni-GDC) composite anodes have been successfully fabricated by aqueous-based tape casting method for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The pre-sintered anode green tape was coated with a GDC electrolyte film by spray coating method and then co-sintered together to obtain electrolyte/anode bi-layer.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The cathode, which is made of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8O3-GDC (LSCF-GDC) was screen printed onto the electrolyte film and sintered to form a complete anode-supported SOFC.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The performance of the cell was evaluated on an in-house developed test station between 500 and 650 degrees C. Due to the limitation of the test station for large-cell testing, small-size samples with dimensions of 2.5 cm x 2.5 cm were cut out from the large-cell.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: For the single cell with humidified hydrogen as fuel and air as oxidant, the maximum power density achieved 909, 623, 335 and 168 mW cm(-2) at 650, 600, 550 and 500 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Impedance analysis confirmed that the performance of single cells below 600 degrees C was retarded primarily due to the slow interfacial reaction kinetics at reduced temperatures.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Development of catalytically active electrode materials, especially the cathode material and improvement of the electrode microstructure are thus crucial for achieving a high performance low-temperature SOFC.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of Ni-GDC composite anode prepared by aqueous-based tape casting method for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell
